at a high level. And then future councils, future subcommittees could always review and continue to push the boundaries to get further along, to get to the ultimate goal. There's no reason why this subcommittee and or the city council couldn't keep these notes for a future point and make sure that it's passed down through the city clerk's office so that it's inherited by future councils

